	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-03-27T01:29:11">Leaf Clean Energy Company (Leaf) is an investment company. The Company, through its subsidiaries, engages in providing hydro energy, landfill gas, biomass and solar energy. The Company invests in clean energy projects in North America. The Company includes activities, such as the production of alternative fuels, renewable power generation and the use of technologies to reduce the environmental impact of traditional energy. The Companys subsidiaries include Energia Escalona Coopertief U.A, Escalona B.V, Energiia Escalona I S.A. de C.V, Energia Escalona s.r.l., Johnstown Regional Energy LLC, Multitrade Rabun Gap LLC, Multitrade Telogia LLC, Telogia Power LLC and SkyFuel Inc.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-11-02T00:04:12">BRIEF: For the fiscal year ended 30 June 2015, Leaf Clean Energy Company revenues increased from -$62.2M to $18.7M. Net income totaled $4.5M vs. loss of $67.9M. Revenues reflect Net foreign exchange loss increase of 50% to -$6K. Net Income reflects Directors Remuneration decrease of 49% to $1.3M (expense), Legal and Professional Fees decrease of 69% to $394K (expense), Travel &amp; subsistence expenses decrease of 76% to $144K (expense).</Text>
